description: {"blocks":[{"key":"e0s7k","text":"Schistosomiasis keeps devastating the world despite many measures put in place by control programs. Molecular diagnostics has played a significant role in the detection and monitoring of the treatment of the disease. Loop-medicated isothermal amplification has been developed with increased sensitivity and specificity to help the diagnosis of schistosomiasis. This protocol aids the successful isolation of schistosome DNA from urine and stool using Quick-DNA Miniprep kits (ZymoResearch, USA) with slight modification. Progressively, specific-specific Schisto-LAMP assay has been developed from the cytochrome c oxidase subunit 1 (COX1) gene of the schistosome mitochondrial genome. In addition, to effectively detect successful amplification, a laboratory-based colorimetric buffer which is pH dependent, was used. The neutral red dye changes from pale yellow to pink when positive and to a deep yellow color if negative. This protocol spells out the performance of two LAMP assays to detect S. haematobium and S. mansoni in urine and stool, respectively. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"italic","offset":995,"length":14},{"style":"italic","offset":1014,"length":10}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

steps.section: Agarose Gel Electrophoresis Protocol
steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"6j37b","text":"The successful LAMP amplification can be confirmed with agarose gel electrophoresis and visualized under UV light. The steps for the gel preparation is as follows;  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

cases.title: Reagent Preparation
cases.description: {"blocks":[{"key":"apks9","text":"10N NaOH: Dissolve 40g of NaOH pellets in 100 ml of dH2O.","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":54,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"d21a5","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"547ng","text":"500ml EDTA (Ph = 8.0): ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2bl88","text":"      Disodium ethylenediamine tetraacetate.2H2O (EDTA) – 372.24gmol-1","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":46,"length":1,"style":"sub"},{"offset":68,"length":2,"style":"sup"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"dmeq3","text":"                Dissolve 93.06g EDTA in 350ml of dH2O","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":51,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"38ju5","text":"                Adjust the pH finally to 8.0 with NaOH.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"frm16","text":"                Top up the solution to 500ml with dH2O and autoclave","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":52,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8suea","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"84v6g","text":"50X TAE (Tris-Acetate-EDTA) Buffer – 500ml ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"fh603","text":"Dissolve; ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e4235","text":"                121g of Tris-Base in 300ml of dH2O","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":48,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e4i68","text":"                Carefully add 28.55ml of Acetic acid (100%)","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"b9qbt","text":"                Add 50ml 0.5M EDTA (pH=8.0)","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9u1a3","text":"                Mix well to dissolve completely","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"c6ub9","text":"                Bring the volume to 500ml using dH2O","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":50,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"567fo","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"crns2","text":"1X TAE (Tris-Acetate-EDTA) Buffer","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"egtsf","text":"                For 1000ml(1L); add 20ml of 50X TAE to 980ml of dH2O","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":66,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"552vq","text":"                (Note: use this for gel preparation and gel running buffer) ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"84r7u","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"7m4nr","text":"10mg/ml Ethidium Bromide (EtBr)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"btduj","text":"                Dissolve 0.2g ethidium bromide in 20 mL dH2O. Mix well and store @ 4C in the dark.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":58,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52vth","text":"                (Note: EtBr is mutagenic and must be handled with care)","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"auh3","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"52pee","text":"6X DNA Loading dye Preparation (10ml)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"btmsf","text":"                Dissolve 25mg of Bromophenol Blue in 6.7 ml of ddH2O.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"offset":66,"length":1,"style":"sub"}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8n9vi","text":"                Add 25mg of Xylene Cyanol FF and mix.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"8sipl","text":"                Add 3.3 ml of glycerol and mix well.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9l6nf","text":"                Aliquot and freeze at -20ºC. ","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6ptrk","text":"DNA Ladder reconstitution (From Thermo-Scientific)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"f9abo","text":"                   Using the ratio of 5:9:11, add 5µl of the DNA Ladder and 9µl of the 6X DNA Loading dye to 11µl of Nuclease-free water to make a total volume of 25µl.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9k69a","text":"                   Pulse vortex and centrifuge at 8000rpm for 30 secs. cases.title: Gel Pre-Staining
cases.description: {"blocks":[{"key":"bhuvr","text":"Ethidium bromide Stain (10mg/ml)","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6tsdt","text":"    Add 5-10 µl of stock per 100ml gel solution (100ml of 1X TBE with agarose powder) to make a final conc. of 0.5-1.0 µg/ml.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

cases.title: Gel Preparation Procedure
cases.description: {"blocks":[{"key":"1quav","text":"To prepare 100 ml of a 2% agarose solution, measure 2g or 1.5 g agarose into a glass beaker or flask and add 100 ml 1X TAE buffer. Microwave or stir on a hot plate until agarose is dissolved and the solution is clear (2 mins).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bie0b","text":"Allow the solution to cool to about 50- 60°C before pouring. ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"lg7o","text":"Add 5-10 µl of 10mg/ml EtBr to make a final concentration of 0.5-1.0 μg/ml.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"deol","text":"Prepare the gel tray by sealing the ends with tape or use a custom-made dam. Place the comb in a gel tray about 1 inch from one end of the tray and position the comb vertically so that the teeth are about 1-2 mm above the tray's surface.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9s9hp","text":"Pour 50°C gel solution into the tray to a depth of about 5 mm. Allow the gel to solidify for about 20 to 30 minutes at room temperature.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2nse3","text":"To run, gently remove the comb, place the tray in the electrophoresis chamber, and cover (just until wells are submerged) with electrophoresis buffer (the same buffer used to prepare the agarose).","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2nfg1","text":"To prepare samples for electrophoresis, add 1μl of 6x gel loading dye for every 5μl of DNA solution. Mix well. Load 5-12μl of DNA per well (for minigel). ","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"afdst","text":"Add a reference DNA ladder (2-4μl) and electrophorese at 70-100 volts until dye markers have migrated an appropriate distance, depending on the size of the DNA to be visualized.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"e0d80","text":"Visualize gel under short-wave UV light and save the image.","type":"ordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
